[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-08 16:16:01.000000000', 'files': ['zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': 'Remove non-voting gate-horizon-dsvm-integration from gate queue

The gate-horizon-dsvm-integration job is now non-voting since
it fails randomly, a lot, as shown by the uncategorized bugs page:

http://status.openstack.org/elastic-recheck/data/uncategorized.html

Having a non-voting job in the gate queue is kind of pointless and
since the uncategorized bugs page is only on gate queue failures,
this job is skewing our categorization rates, so remove it from
the gate.

Change-Id: I433611a3533a1c80726b610de0b8ca46fc6b9485
'}]
commit_message:
Remove non-voting gate-horizon-dsvm-integration from gate queue

The gate-horizon-dsvm-integration job is now non-voting since
it fails randomly, a lot, as shown by the uncategorized bugs page:

http://status.openstack.org/elastic-recheck/data/uncategorized.html

Having a non-voting job in the gate queue is kind of pointless and
since the uncategorized bugs page is only on gate queue failures,
this job is skewing our categorization rates, so remove it from
the gate.

Change-Id: I433611a3533a1c80726b610de0b8ca46fc6b9485

commit_message:
Ironicclient minimum is too low for nova virt

Nova virt in kilo uses the 'configdrive' parameter, which did not exist
before v0.4.0. Since 0.4.0 was broken, we will set it to >=0.4.1.

Closes-Bug: #1470950
Change-Id: I2b6734883a27d3d9850a09a4c60e4e0ccb180abf

commit_message:
Switch to use local.conf for DevStack runs

We're needing to start setting values in config files via local.conf's
post-config sections, so switch to generating local.conf instead
of localrc.

I fully expect the Grenade jobs to fail at this point, Grenade will
need to be updated to handle either file.

Change-Id: I33f9da2b7f363b9d1e0c1f2bb4c26da47ba30bcd

commit_message:
Allow libvirt cleanup completion when serial ports already released

Libvirt driver cleanup changed with try-except to be tolerant of
InstanceNotFound exceptions when attempting to fetch missing ports
(possibly removed on a previous cleanup).

Closes-Bug: 1450594

commit_message:
VMware: Add vmware:adapter_type extra spec

The following patch adds an additional extra spec,
"vmware:adapter_type", which can be specified to choose the
storage controller a volume will use. The choices are:
busLogic, ide, lsiLogic, or lsiLogicsas. If the extra spec is
not specified, the default adapter_type will be lsiLogic.

If the cinder volume is created from a Glance image, the
adapter_type will be defined using the image metadata (i.e.
vmware_adaptertype), if one is specified. Otherwise, it should
be set to the vmware:adapter_type extra spec (if one is
specified) or default to lsiLogic.

DocImpact: New volume type extra spec (vmware:adapter_type)
for VMware VMDK driver

commit_message:
Changes conf.py for Sphinx build because oslosphinx now contains GA

- Changes api to API to force build of all source files.
- Ensures tracking is consistent across all openstack.org web properties.
- Tracks only docs.openstack.org/developer/{{ project }} where
project name is taken from conf.py.
- Removes ability to build local without GA. If you have ideas
for how to build local without GA, please patch.

Change-Id: Ibb61e5c1668e6a0782daf91d4faf0950c5bf77d7
Partial-bug: 1441315

commit_message:
Remove unneeded OS_TEST_DBAPI_ADMIN_CONNECTION

The desired OS_TEST_DBAPI_ADMIN_CONNECTION string is now reflected
in the oslo.db 1.12.0 release's default behavior, and so does not
need to be set any longer to achieve the same opportunistic backend
discovery for tests.

subject: Have all os-refresh-config elements use su instead of sudo
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-05-19 20:47:32.000000000', 'files': ['elements/nova-api/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-nova-db-sync', 'elements/trove-api/os-refresh-config/post-configure.d/82-trove-api', 'elements/ironic-api/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-ironic-db-sync', 'elements/nova-baremetal/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-nova-baremetal-db-sync', 'elements/ceilometer-api/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-ceilometer-db-sync', 'elements/tuskar/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-tuskar-db-sync', 'elements/glance/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-glance-db-sync', 'elements/keystone/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-keystone-db-sync', 'elements/heat-engine/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-heat-db-sync', 'elements/cinder-api/os-refresh-config/configure.d/90-cinder-db-sync'], 'message': 'Have all os-refresh-config elements use su instead of sudo

Using sudo -u to change users for a command can fail if sudo thinks it needs
a controlling TTY as part of its authentication.  Since this is the default config,
that means that whenever the command is run in an environment that does not have
a TTY (such as from init(1)), sudo will die.

su does not care or check for a controlling TTY, so it will succeed as long as
it is being run by root (which should be the case for all os-refresh-config elements).

Therefore, instead of using sudo -u <username> -- <command> to run commands as other
users, use su -s /bin/bash -c "<command>" <username>

This will allow things to function in the face of a misconfigured sudo as well as
allow commands to run against an account that has been locked out or has a shell
that otherwise restricts what commands can be run.

Change-Id: I5cc518ce42536a09e9f25c6635e191884aaaef92
'}]
commit_message:
Have all os-refresh-config elements use su instead of sudo

Using sudo -u to change users for a command can fail if sudo thinks it needs
a controlling TTY as part of its authentication.  Since this is the default config,
that means that whenever the command is run in an environment that does not have
a TTY (such as from init(1)), sudo will die.

su does not care or check for a controlling TTY, so it will succeed as long as
it is being run by root (which should be the case for all os-refresh-config elements).

Therefore, instead of using sudo -u <username> -- <command> to run commands as other
users, use su -s /bin/bash -c "<command>" <username>

This will allow things to function in the face of a misconfigured sudo as well as
allow commands to run against an account that has been locked out or has a shell
that otherwise restricts what commands can be run.

Change-Id: I5cc518ce42536a09e9f25c6635e191884aaaef92

2) go to the 'Next page'
3) Click create environment

commit_message:
Pin oslo.i18n for keystoneclient

oslo.i18n 2.0.0 is installed by keystoneclient.
It doesn't have 'oslo' namespace which is still used
in our version of keystoneclient so we need to use older release.

Change-Id: I6fa92f035a6f962217032e0b007cdc559d29f8fb
Closes-Bug: #1469050

commit_message:
Add scheduler_driver parameter to nova::scheduler class

commit_message:
keystone/auth: make service description configurable

This commit adds the service description as a class parameter in order to allow
users to update from a previous version if the service description is changed
(incorrectly spelled or wrong description).

This commit also fix the Ironic service description, 'Ironic Networking Service'
seems to be a too quick sed of a neutron manifest.

commit_message:
Document Listener and Manage Entrypoints Dev Docs

Per: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/196750/2

The entrypoints were updated:

Renames 'index' entrypoint (and cmd) to 'manage', and adds a command
'index' whose current only subcommand is 'sync' (with the intent that
we'll add more, like testing how in-sync things are).

Adds an entry point 'listener' for the notification listener, and
renames that cmd to 'listener'.

Partial-Bug: #1471955

Neutron constant COMMON_PREFIXES does not exist anymore

constants.

commit_message:
Use module install script for acceptance tests

This patch updates the spec_helper_acceptance.rb file to use the common
module install script and Puppetfile from the new
openstack/puppet-openstack-integration repo. This will allow us to take
advantage of Zuul's Depends-On feature so that we can test changes
across multiple related modules. This is based on idea 1 from this
brainstorming session[1].

This will probably be abstracted out into a separate function or
eventually a separate gem so that it can be more easily shared across
the OpenStack modules and the Infra modules.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/puppet-git-dependencies

Change-Id: I5d4b3be59823dcf58e157cb7ac54797b6322f1eb
Co-Authored-By: James E. Blair <jeblair@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Spencer Krum <spencer.krum@hp.com>

Using the new multi-user support, add functional tests to exercise

   In Project A: Admin, Creator, Observer, Auditor

commit_message:
Add Functional Tests for ACLs Using Multiple Users

Using the new multi-user support, add functional tests to exercise
secret and container GETs for different users and different configured
ACLs.

Six users with four roles in two projects are used:
   In Project A: Admin, Creator, Observer, Auditor
   In Project B: Admin, Observer

Five ACL scenarios are tested:
   No ACL: default
   RBAC Only: project-acess is True, ACL is empty
   Creator Only: project-access is False, ACL is empty
   ACL Only: project-access is False, ACL has a user
   RBAC + ACL: project-access is TruA, ACL has a user

Get Secrets and Get Containers are tested for each user in each scenario.

Implements: blueprint multi-user-functional-tests

commit_message:
Use module install script for acceptance tests

This patch updates the spec_helper_acceptance.rb file to use the common
module install script and Puppetfile from the new
openstack/puppet-openstack-integration repo. This will allow us to take
advantage of Zuul's Depends-On feature so that we can test changes
across multiple related modules. This is based on idea 1 from this
brainstorming session[1].

This will probably be abstracted out into a separate function or
eventually a separate gem so that it can be more easily shared across
the OpenStack modules and the Infra modules.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/puppet-git-dependencies

commit_message:
Correct `puppet module list` check in beaker

The final check during the prep stage, where `puppet module list` is
run so that its output can be used for debugging, should run on the
current host in the loop, not the first host in the array.

commit_message:
Add Barbican key manager

Adds the first usable key manager plugin to Castellan. While there is an
implementation of a mock key manager in the test directories, it is used
only for testing.

This code is based on the barbican key manager code in Nova written by
Brianna Poulos. See: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/104001/

The Barbican API version info will be read from a config option until
the Barbican Version API is fixed.  See fix-version-api blueprint.

Implements: blueprint add-barbican-key-manager
Co-authored-by: Brianna Poulos <brianna.poulos@jhuapl.edu>
Change-Id: Ia27cd831f42c6b027778240b3396b1c4149dc689

subject: Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-07-07 21:58:17.000000000', 'files': ['Gemfile', 'spec/spec_helper_acceptance.rb'], 'message': "Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: I2cb734defce21ed1709e80bd0f0b0d965b772a9d
"}]
commit_message:
Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: I2cb734defce21ed1709e80bd0f0b0d965b772a9d

commit_message:
Use module install script for acceptance tests

This patch updates the spec_helper_acceptance.rb file to use the common
module install script and Puppetfile from the new
openstack/puppet-openstack-integration repo. This will allow us to take
advantage of Zuul's Depends-On feature so that we can test changes
across multiple related modules. This is based on idea 1 from this
brainstorming session[1].

This will probably be abstracted out into a separate function or
eventually a separate gem so that it can be more easily shared across
the OpenStack modules and the Infra modules.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/puppet-git-dependencies

commit_message:
IBP: fuel-agent should preserve free space in produced images

As for now, fuel-agent produces images which were shrunk to the minimum
filesystem size. Therefore, it could result in a file system which is not
optimized for speed.

This change will allow to control the amount of preserved free space in
produced images.

Additionally, it enlarges /boot partition size to 300M in order to fit newly
produced images into /boot partition size.

Change-Id: I8a2fd71f33b15de49b2854b03672e1c2eec4979d
Closes-Bug: #1469155

subject: Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-07 21:23:28.000000000', 'files': ['Gemfile', 'spec/spec_helper_acceptance.rb'], 'message': "Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: If12404d692b4ad5bf3d536f58e7a553ebf014ce3
"}]
commit_message:
Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: If12404d692b4ad5bf3d536f58e7a553ebf014ce3

commit_message:
Remove invalid skipping of tests

One of the tests in the test_validators suite was being skipped in
reference to a bug that was deemed invalid. So skipping it wasn't the
appropriate thing to do. Now that's not the case.

The other one was reffering to a feature that has already been
implemented, therefore we can stop skipping that test.

Change-Id: Ia068ff04ab1ea79b77727ad388720692c83df8cf

commit_message:
Use module install script for acceptance tests

This patch updates the spec_helper_acceptance.rb file to use the common
module install script and Puppetfile from the new
openstack/puppet-openstack-integration repo. This will allow us to take
advantage of Zuul's Depends-On feature so that we can test changes
across multiple related modules. This is based on idea 1 from this
brainstorming session[1].

This will probably be abstracted out into a separate function or
eventually a separate gem so that it can be more easily shared across
the OpenStack modules and the Infra modules.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/puppet-git-dependencies

Change-Id: I9f9b8b4425a6227853a53fee9e460a75dfa07326
Co-Authored-By: James E. Blair <jeblair@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Spencer Krum <spencer.krum@hp.com>

subject: Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-07 20:54:05.000000000', 'files': ['Gemfile', 'spec/spec_helper_acceptance.rb'], 'message': "Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: I366f6b607e348d2fdd1fd59afbbe4908f485aab3
"}]
commit_message:
Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: I366f6b607e348d2fdd1fd59afbbe4908f485aab3

commit_message:
Bump YAQL version to 0.2.7

YAQL version 0.2.7 have a few critical bugfixes. So according this
we need to bump YAQL version from 0.2.6 to 0.2.7 in global-requirements
and upper-constraints.
Also, the YAQL 0.2.6 haven't compatibility with ply 3.6, which listed in
upper-constraints. This problem blocks murano-dsvm-gate.

Change-Id: Icc5e0d249d1f8661980b5321e96702d5e97de767

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-06-18 10:45:29.000000000', 'files': ['lib/puppet/provider/neutron_router/neutron.rb', 'spec/unit/provider/neutron_router/neutron_spec.rb'], 'message': "Fix parsing of network gateway id for router

The neutron router-show command with shell formating outputs the
external_gateway_info with literal backslashes to escape the double
quotes. The provider must then match against the literal slashes when

commit_message:
Fix parsing of network gateway id for router

The neutron router-show command with shell formating outputs the
external_gateway_info with literal backslashes to escape the double
quotes. The provider must then match against the literal slashes when
extracting the gateway id. If this is not done, the provider cannot
detect the gateway id from the external_gateway_info property and will
always attempt to change the gateway name from '' to the desired name.

Change-Id: I85a18ed08886cebd14f61b65b3681a75a8d41741

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:
Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: I5d70949b29e97688989fddd03c667d601c927811

commit_message:
Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:
Use beaker-puppet_install_helper to install puppet

When running with BEAKER_provision=no, the following happens:

In Trusty: beaker is running dpkg with '--force' option so even
if Puppet is already installed, the return code will be 0.
In CentOS: beaker is running 'rpm -ivh' the second time and since
the package is already here, the return code will be 1.

Using the new puppet install helper will abort installing puppet
if BEAKER_provision is no, so tests will continue as normal.

Change-Id: I5d70949b29e97688989fddd03c667d601c927811

commit_message:
Optionally create trust for alarm actions

When creating actions using TrustRestAlarmNotifier, allow the absence of
trust ID and automatically creates a trust in this case for the
ceilometer service user. This enables creation of trust alarms without
knowing the ceilometer service user ID outside of ceilometer itself.

blueprint trust-alarm-notifier
Change-Id: I4b781cbdd46dd4574fea44b40adad869373ab344
